<p>I have an MVC2 application. I have the following view, controller and model:</p>  <p>This what I have in my view:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;%using (Html.BeginForm()) { %&gt; &lt;div&gt;   &lt;fieldset&gt;         &lt;legend&gt;E-Safe Information&lt;/legend&gt;             &lt;div id="message" style="height:10px; margin-bottom:10px"&gt;                 &lt;%:Html.ValidationSummary(true, "Creation of Data failed. Please correct errors and try again.") %&gt;             &lt;/div&gt;             &lt;%:ViewData["Message"] %&gt;             &lt;table&gt;                 &lt;tr&gt;                     &lt;td&gt;&lt;div class="editor-label"&gt;&lt;%: Html.LabelFor(m =&gt; m.Corporation) %&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;                     &lt;td&gt;&lt;div class="editor-field"&gt;&lt;%: Html.TextBoxFor(m =&gt; m.Corporation)%&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;                     &lt;td&gt;&lt;%: Html.ValidationMessageFor(m =&gt; m.Corporation) %&gt;&lt;/td&gt;                 &lt;/tr&gt;                 &lt;tr&gt;                     &lt;td&gt;&lt;div class="editor-label"&gt;&lt;%: Html.LabelFor(m =&gt; m.Region) %&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;                     &lt;td&gt;&lt;div class="editor-field"&gt;&lt;%: Html.TextBoxFor(m =&gt; m.Region, new { @id = "regionTextBox", maxlength = 2 })%&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;                     &lt;td&gt;&lt;%: Html.ValidationMessageFor(m =&gt; m.Region) %&gt;&lt;/td&gt;                 &lt;/tr&gt;                 &lt;tr&gt;                     &lt;td&gt;&lt;div class="editor-label"&gt;&lt;%: Html.LabelFor(m =&gt; m.PortfolioName) %&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;                     &lt;td&gt;&lt;div class="editor-field"&gt;&lt;%: Html.TextBoxFor(m =&gt; m.PortfolioName) %&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;                     &lt;td&gt;&lt;%: Html.ValidationMessageFor(m =&gt; m.PortfolioName) %&gt;&lt;/td&gt;                 &lt;/tr&gt;                 &lt;tr&gt;                     &lt;td&gt; &lt;input type="submit" value="Create" /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;                 &lt;/tr&gt;             &lt;/table&gt;     &lt;/fieldset&gt; &lt;/div&gt;             </code></pre>    <p>The what I have in my controller for this view</p>  <pre><code>[HttpPost] public ActionResult Index(EsafeModel model) {     if (ModelState.IsValid)     {         if (EsafeService.ValidateEsafeData(model.Corporation, model.Region, model.PortfolioName))         {             if (EsafeService.Create(model.Corporation, model.Region, model.PortfolioName))             {                 ViewData["Message"] = "Data created!!!";             }         }         else         {             ModelState.AddModelError("", "The data provided is incorrect.");         }     }     return View(model); } </code></pre>  <p>After "Create" button is clicked, I display error in <code>Validation Summary</code> if no data is provided. If data is provided but does not meet the validation requirements, I also want to display the appropriate message, but I want this message to be displayed in <code>Validation Summary</code> area. Now, if the error is displayed, it is building the list of errors that overlaps the form control.</p>  <p>What would be the best way to change <code>ValidationSummary</code> message inside of a <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> tag?</p>  <p>Thank's</p>